The paper deals with the problem of exploring an anonymous graph, which is a topic in graph theory and algorithms. The use of memory and traversal of edges suggests a connection to data structures and algorithms. The exploration of graphs is also relevant to robotics and autonomous systems, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the optimality of the Rotor-Router algorithm, which is related to optimization and complexity theory (cs.DM, cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the exploration of graphs with unknown parameters, which is related to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.SI).
